CEZ Rises Fourth Day After BofA Merrill Lynch Recommends Buying

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-28T08:23:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/cez-rises-fourth-day-after-bofa-merrill-lynch-recommends-buying.html
CEZ AS (CEZ)  jumped for a fourth day to a
two-month high after Bank of America Merrill Lynch upgraded the
largest Czech power utility to “buy” from “neutral” today,
citing an increased forecast for electricity prices.  CEZ rallied 1.3 percent to 874.1 koruna by 10:10 a.m. in
 Prague , its highest intraday price since Jan. 25. The stock has
gained 7.9 percent so far in March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  